row.entry:
The rules in Division 1
(rr 46.1–46.9
) apply generally. The remaining rules in this Part only apply to proceedings in the Equity Division of the Supreme Court. This part does not apply to the Industrial Relations Commission (when constituted otherwise than as the Industrial Court): see r 1.5 and Sch 1.

p.text:
The accounting party is liable to be cross-examined by the non-accounting party on his accounts before surcharges and falsifications (see 
[46.7.5]
) are filed, and this right is usually reflected in directions which are given under this Part: see Wormsley v Sturt (1856) 22 Beav 398; 52 ER 1161 ; Lord v Lord (1866) LR 2 Eq 605; Meacham v Cooper (1873) LR 16 Eq 102; Arons v McInerny (No 2) (1899) 25 VLR 210  and Hagan v Waterhouse [1983] 2 NSWLR 395.
